      public OrganizerEvent()

    • OrganizerEvent

      public OrganizerEvent(String eventId, String organizerId, String EventTitle, String description, String startDate, String endDate, String location, String limitGuests, String link, String qrCode, String organizerEmail, String posterURL)
      Creates a fully-initialized OrganizerEvent object.
      Parameters:
      eventId - Unique ID of the event.
      organizerId - ID of the organizer who created the event.
      EventTitle - Name/title of the event.
      description - Description or details about the event.
      startDate - Event start date.
      endDate - Event end date.
      location - Location where the event will take place.
      limitGuests - Maximum number of allowed attendees.
      link - Optional link associated with the event.
      qrCode - Base64-encoded QR code used for event check-in.
      organizerEmail - Organizer's contact email.
      posterURL - URL of the uploaded event poster image (nullable).
